settings.heading: Blue Marine Foundation
settings.desc: Blue Marine is a UK registered charity set up in 2010 by some of the team behind the award-winning documentary film ‘The End of the Line’. Working on a vast number of projects across the globe, their aim is to restore the ocean to health by addressing overfishing, one of the world’s biggest environmental problems.
settings.story: Blue Marine’s mission is to see 30% of the world’s ocean under effective protection by 2030. They are dedicated to creating marine reserves, restoring vital habitats and establishing models of sustainable fishing. This collection exists specifically to support their important work supporting sea turtle hatchlings in the Dutch Caribbean.

settings.heading: Silhouettes
settings.desc: Be organised for every occasion with accessories designed to make life a little easier and more luxurious.

settings.heading: Elizabeth Scarlett
settings.desc: Elizabeth started building Elizabeth Scarlett in 2015, painting beautiful watercolours that were then translated onto gorgeous fabrics with intricate embroidery. To this day, every pattern, symbol or motif comes from one of Elizabeth’s original paintings.
settings.story: Turtles play an incredibly important role in the underwater world; from providing key habitats for other threatened marine life to balancing the nutrients of the delicate beach ecosystem and sustaining the food web. I’m so excited that with your help, we’ll be able to do our own special bit for this species, while also spreading a little joy with bright colours and bold new designs!

settings.heading: Luxury Gift Boxes
settings.desc: Treating someone special? Our gold-foiled gift boxes and hand-illustrated note cards make it easy to create a unique and extra special gifting experience. Simply add at the checkout.

settings.infotext: *Supporting our 2% to the wild initiative, 2% from every item in our Island Paradise Collection and 10% of the sales of turtle range will be donated to the Blue Marine Foundation and will be allocated to St Maarten and St Eustatius projects. We will endeavour to direct the funds raised from your purchase to benefit turtles, however, any surplus funds will go towards their wider marine conservation initiatives.
